o me! I I who breathe but God who breathes in me.\") is this \"shared, common essence\" that it simultaneously exists in Acts AD 70 + USA 1974. perception of it is an intellectual matter having to do with conceptualization, abstrac tion + a very high order of reasoning, not revelation. This is an eidos that is a person A person has acquired the status of a Platonist eidos. It now therefore can instantiate itself (although imperfectly) in many particulars at many times + places. To rouse a particular conception) discovery of its own true nature \"as\" Christ (but only imperfectly; that is to inferring conceptually back from its own self as particular to Christ its eidos) Christ could I theorize) cause the particular human to encounte one other particular, at another time + space also based on this same eidos (i.e. on Christ him. self) because then the meta-abstraction (Plato's anamnesis) would occur + recovery of the forms, specifically of the Form from which the two particular humans derive their common essence How is this done? The initiative is taken by Christ as eidos; it is not something that happens by accident or that the particular achieves by work, study, introspection + effort. Here is where the Gnostic story \"the legend of the Pearl\" comes in, + especially the salvator salvandus, since in saving the person (particular) Christ is so-to speak saving himself in that it is he Who is in the person unrecognized as if the-person is asleep + has K-62 forgotten (but in fact he never knew qua person; he only knew qua Christ). Thus remembering, knowing + being Christ are 3 ways of expressing the same thing. What strikes me (regarding how this is done) is that when you recover a form you recover all forms; that is, you think + see in a different way. Platonist anamnesis as such should, then, do it. The argument here is in fact to Cartesian rationalism, that we possess innate categories which remain latent until triggered into activity + consciousness. It could well 